on. 

From your question, it seems you may be referring to 'squalene'. Although Squalane and Squalene sound very similar and have their benefits on the skin, they differ in their origin and composition. 

Squalene is a natural compound found in certain plants, commercially obtained from fish oils, specifically shark liver oil. Squalane is a hydrocarbon that is sustainably sourced from sugarcane. 

